00:56:21,511 --> 00:56:24,446
That's my terminology for getting rid
of the birth controls...

505
00:56:24,581 --> 00:56:26,105
pulling the goalie.

506
00:56:26,249 --> 00:56:28,080
Yeah, of course.

507
00:56:28,218 --> 00:56:30,277
Everything's in
hockey terms, you know.

508
00:56:30,420 --> 00:56:32,285
At least you'll have
a good time going there.

509
00:56:32,422 --> 00:56:35,220
Oh, dear.

510
00:56:35,358 --> 00:56:37,849
Is that the names
you're thinking of?

511
00:56:37,994 --> 00:56:40,258
Now what do you want?
Do you want a boy or a girl?

512
00:56:40,397 --> 00:56:43,161
Just healthy.

513
00:56:43,299 --> 00:56:45,859
- I'll give you a hand.
- Thanks.

514
00:56:49,005 --> 00:56:51,496
So, I was thinking

515
00:56:51,641 --> 00:56:53,836
that maybe we could do this
for you a couple times a week.

516
00:56:53,977 --> 00:56:57,936
'Cause I know you've been spending
a lot of time with your mom lately.

517
00:56:58,081 --> 00:57:01,312
I thought it might be easier for you
if you didn't have to worry about cooking.

518
00:57:02,619 --> 00:57:06,055
That is unless you think
you'd get sick of us.

519
00:57:06,189 --> 00:57:08,453
I mean, we'd understand
if you wanted to be alone.

520
00:57:18,001 --> 00:57:19,468
You okay?

521
00:57:22,572 --> 00:57:24,802
Yeah. I'll be right back, Sarah.

522
00:57:43,092 --> 00:57:44,684
It's okay.

523
00:57:46,062 --> 00:57:48,155
It's okay. It's nothing.

524
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:53,929
- We're gonna get home and be hungry again.
- You know it.

525
00:57:54,070 --> 00:57:56,834
- I know it.
- You okay, honey?

526
00:57:56,973 --> 00:58:00,409
Yeah. Anybody
want some coffee?

527
00:58:26,503 --> 00:58:28,300
What's wrong?

528
00:58:33,109 --> 00:58:34,701
Nothing.

529
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:07,703
Travis, you're hurting me!

530
00:59:07,844 --> 00:59:09,778
Travis, stop!

531
00:59:12,248 --> 00:59:13,875
I'm sorry.

532
00:59:16,252 --> 00:59:19,949
Would you please tell me
what's wrong?

533
00:59:20,089 --> 00:59:24,150
God, I know you're upset about your mom,
but don't take your frustration out on me!

534
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:31,796
Ever since she got sick,
you've... you've shut down.

535
00:59:34,971 --> 00:59:37,531
Would you say something,
please!

536
01:00:08,738 --> 01:00:11,571
I am so sorry about last night.

537
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:15,437
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

538
01:00:15,578 --> 01:00:18,240
I don't know why I did that.

539
01:00:18,381 --> 01:00:21,839
But I promise you
it will never happen again.

540
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:30,058
Okay.

541
01:00:30,193 --> 01:00:33,219
I just need you to talk to me and tell me
what's going on in your head, okay?

542
01:00:33,363 --> 01:00:35,024
Okay.

543
01:01:22,545 --> 01:01:25,571
- Hey.
- Hey.

544
01:01:25,715 --> 01:01:27,649
How you feeling?

545
01:01:28,718 --> 01:01:31,881
Oh, I feel fine.

546
01:01:32,021 --> 01:01:35,957
Good. I want you to feel fine.

547
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:42,892
Where's Lorraine?

548
01:01:44,133 --> 01:01:46,260
She's in the kitchen.

549
01:01:48,738 --> 01:01:50,501
Oh.

550
01:01:51,741 --> 01:01:54,141
You didn't kill her yet?

551
01:01:56,345 --> 01:01:57,972
What?

552
01:02:01,350 --> 01:02:03,784
You didn't kill her yet?

553
01:02:08,624 --> 01:02:10,751
Why are you saying that?

554
01:02:19,102 --> 01:02:20,399
Mom?

555
01:02:22,572 --> 01:02:24,938
'Cause you're a fuckin' murderer!

556
01:02:29,979 --> 01:02:32,038
Is she talking today?

557
01:02:33,316 --> 01:02:34,943
No.

558
01:02:54,737 --> 01:02:57,934
Trav, can we talk for a minute?

559
01:02:58,074 --> 01:03:02,135
My head is killing me.
I really gotta get some sleep.

560
01:03:02,278 --> 01:03:03,745
Okay.

561
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:07,577
I think I'm gonna
stay up for a little while.

562
01:03:07,717 --> 01:03:09,685
Have a good night.

563
01:03:18,494 --> 01:03:21,224
He has no idea what's going on.

564
01:03:29,438 --> 01:03:32,236
Wait till he sees
what we have planned for him.

565
01:03:34,143 --> 01:03:35,735
Lorraine?

566
01:03:40,883 --> 01:03:43,010
He doesn't know.

567
01:03:44,887 --> 01:03:47,617
Lorraine, who are you talking to?

568
01:03:54,330 --> 01:03:55,797
Lorraine?

569
01:03:58,601 --> 01:04:00,592
I'm not Lorraine.

570
01:04:16,085 --> 01:04:18,349
No, I don't know why.

571
01:04:26,762 --> 01:04:29,526
I really wanna talk to you
about all this.

572
01:04:35,771 --> 01:04:37,898
No, he's still sleeping.

573
01:04:41,177 --> 01:04:44,340
Can we get together later?

574
01:04:44,480 --> 01:04:48,382
Thanks. God, I don't know
what I'd do without you right now.

575
01:04:50,753 --> 01:04:53,551
I gotta go. Yeah, bye.

576
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:57,783
Hey.

577
01:04:57,927 --> 01:05:00,122
Who was that?

578
01:05:00,263 --> 01:05:02,060
Just Sarah.

579
01:05:03,666 --> 01:05:05,327
Oh.

580
01:05:05,468 --> 01:05:07,834
How are you feeling
this morning?

581
01:05:09,605 --> 01:05:11,129
Okay.

582
01:05:11,274 --> 01:05:13,572
Are you going to your mom's?

583
01:05:15,244 --> 01:05:17,235
Yeah.

584
01:05:17,380 --> 01:05:19,974
I'll have to meet you there later.

585
01:05:20,116 --> 01:05:23,711
I'm gonna get some groceries.
We're out of everything.

586
01:05:23,853 --> 01:05:25,753
Sure.

587
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:16,434
Yeah, Mom, that's me.

588
01:06:17,974 --> 01:06:20,169
I'm having...

589
01:06:20,309 --> 01:06:23,676
a lot of trouble right now, Mom.

590
01:06:23,813 --> 01:06:27,544
I really wish you had made me
get some help a long time ago.

591
01:06:30,252 --> 01:06:33,085
I'm really scared.

592
01:06:34,457 --> 01:06:36,891
Is he still here?

593
01:06:37,026 --> 01:06:39,324
Who?

594
01:06:39,462 --> 01:06:41,396
Henry.

595
01:06:44,433 --> 01:06:48,494
No, Mom. Henry's been gone
a long time.

596
01:06:49,605 --> 01:06:52,096
He came to visit me.

597
01:06:55,111 --> 01:06:57,341
That's not possible.

598
01:06:57,480 --> 01:06:59,311
Ah, sure it is.

599
01:07:01,250 --> 01:07:02,911
He gave me this.

600
01:07:15,564 --> 01:07:17,725
Have you been talking to Lorraine?

601
01:07:17,867 --> 01:07:19,858
Did she put you up to this?

602
01:07:20,002 --> 01:07:21,492
No.

603
01:07:21,637 --> 01:07:25,038
Who then? Greg?
It was Greg, right?

604
01:07:26,609 --> 01:07:30,909
This is an old sketch.
Henry wasn't here, Mom.

605
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:32,412
Yes, he was.

606
01:07:32,548 --> 01:07:34,914
No, he wasn't!

607
01:07:36,719 --> 01:07:38,482
Is everything okay?

608
01:07:38,621 --> 01:07:40,919
Has anybody else been
to visit my mom recently?

609
01:07:41,057 --> 01:07:42,649
No. Why?

610
01:07:42,792 --> 01:07:45,056
Are you sure
everything's all right?

611
01:07:49,231 --> 01:07:50,630
Lorraine!

612
01:08:10,953 --> 01:08:13,922
<i>You know how his face got like that?</i>

613
01:08:19,528 --> 01:08:21,428
Lorraine!

614
01:08:22,631 --> 01:08:25,293
- Hey, Tami.
- Hi.

615
01:08:25,434 --> 01:08:28,926
- Is Travis back there?
- No. He left a little while ago.

616
01:08:30,072 --> 01:08:32,063
Oh. Thanks.

617
01:09:01,303 --> 01:09:03,396
<i>You better murder this woman</i>.

618
01:09:16,051 --> 01:09:17,746
No!

619
01:10:07,436 --> 01:10:09,427
Who are you?

620
01:10:15,778 --> 01:10:17,643
I know who they want me
to think you are,

621
01:10:17,780 --> 01:10:20,874
but you can tell Lorraine and Greg
that it's not gonna work.

622
01:10:24,053 --> 01:10:27,784
They think that if I lose it, they can just leave
me behind and live happily ever after.

623
01:10:27,923 --> 01:10:29,584
Right?

624
01:10:29,725 --> 01:10:33,126
Well, I know what's real
and what isn't.

625
01:10:34,897 --> 01:10:38,128
I know you're not real!

626
01:10:52,548 --> 01:10:56,609
I just wanted them to feel some
of the pain that I was feeling.

627
01:11:00,756 --> 01:11:03,554
They don't understand
how we feel things.

628
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:10,588
I heard them.
They were planning something.

629
01:11:10,733 --> 01:11:13,793
We had to do it, Henry.

630
01:11:16,772 --> 01:11:19,570
I never wanted
Nadine to get hurt.

631
01:11:21,443 --> 01:11:24,139
I never thought
you'd run like that.

632
01:11:26,348 --> 01:11:29,408
It just didn't happen
the way I wanted it to happen.

633
01:11:36,492 --> 01:11:38,551
I'm sorry, Henry.

634
01:11:39,795 --> 01:11:43,196
I swear, I'm so sorry.

635
01:11:43,365 --> 01:11:45,993
I never wanted you to get hurt.

636
01:11:47,336 --> 01:11:50,965
I always looked out for you.

637
01:11:52,808 --> 01:11:54,742
I looked out for you!

638
01:12:11,560 --> 01:12:14,495
We can't let them know
we're watching them.

639
01:12:16,498 --> 01:12:20,400
They hate us, Henry. I heard them say it.
You have to protect me.

640
01:12:20,569 --> 01:12:22,537
That's my hiding place, dude.

641
01:12:22,671 --> 01:12:26,072
Sorry to spoil your plans, Bobby.

642
01:12:26,208 --> 01:12:28,369
- You're dead, man! You're fuckin' dead!
- Henry!

643
01:12:28,510 --> 01:12:30,705
- Stop it!
- Henry!

644
01:12:30,846 --> 01:12:34,145
What are you doing?
Look out!

645
01:12:59,875 --> 01:13:02,139
Please, Henry.

646
01:13:06,782 --> 01:13:09,114
I can make this right.

647
01:13:29,004 --> 01:13:31,529
Oh, shit.

648
01:13:38,213 --> 01:13:40,147
What time is it, Tami?

649
01:13:40,315 --> 01:13:43,978
It's... It's a little after 1:00.

650
01:13:44,119 --> 01:13:45,780
Thanks.

651
01:14:10,879 --> 01:14:13,040
Hey.

652
01:14:14,082 --> 01:14:15,640
Hey.

653
01:14:16,985 --> 01:14:19,010
What are you doing?

654
01:14:19,154 --> 01:14:21,520
Just taking care of some garbage.

655
01:14:23,559 --> 01:14:26,255
At 3:00 a. M?

656
01:14:26,395 --> 01:14:28,886
I don't feel much like sleeping.

657
01:14:33,335 --> 01:14:34,825
We need to talk.

658
01:14:34,970 --> 01:14:37,837
We do need to talk.

659
01:14:37,973 --> 01:14:40,407
I know what happened to Henry.

660
01:14:41,477 --> 01:14:43,206
I don't think you do.

661
01:14:43,345 --> 01:14:45,313
I do, Travis.

662
01:14:45,447 --> 01:14:49,406
I know about the camping trip...
Lori and Bobby.

663
01:14:49,551 --> 01:14:52,816
- Been talking to Greg, huh?
- And Sarah.

664
01:14:54,056 --> 01:14:55,580
I know everything.

665
01:14:56,658 --> 01:14:58,455
Not everything.

666
01:15:00,496 --> 01:15:02,964
Look, this is it.

667
01:15:04,233 --> 01:15:07,691
If you can't open up
to me right now,

668
01:15:07,836 --> 01:15:10,031
then I'm leaving.

669
01:15:10,172 --> 01:15:13,005
I need to know why
you're so angry with me,

670
01:15:13,141 --> 01:15:16,167
why you won't talk
to me anymore.

671
01:15:16,311 --> 01:15:18,575
I wanna know everything.

672
01:15:27,322 --> 01:15:29,256
You gonna get that?

673
01:15:33,562 --> 01:15:34,961
Hello?

674
01:15:37,766 --> 01:15:40,701
No, he's not with us.

675
01:15:40,836 --> 01:15:42,827
Okay, hang on.

676
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:47,707
Have you seen Greg?
Sarah hasn't seen him all night.

677
01:15:49,811 --> 01:15:52,041
I'm sure he's around.

678
01:15:56,919 --> 01:15:59,479
No, he hasn't seen him either.

679
01:15:59,621 --> 01:16:02,283
Okay, call us back.

680
01:16:05,527 --> 01:16:08,496
She's pretty freaked out.
He never does this.

681
01:16:08,630 --> 01:16:11,428
Well, you never know
what people are gonna do.

682
01:16:13,101 --> 01:16:15,433
What does that mean?

683
01:16:15,571 --> 01:16:18,369
It means you should never make the mistake
of giving someone your trust,

684
01:16:18,507 --> 01:16:23,240
your heart, because you never know
what they're gonna do with it.

685
01:16:23,378 --> 01:16:25,812
Why are you being like this?

686
01:16:28,283 --> 01:16:31,650
Will you please tell me what's wrong?
I can't help you if you don't tell me.

687
01:16:31,787 --> 01:16:35,382
Lorraine, there's so much wrong
I wouldn't even know where to begin.

688
01:16:35,524 --> 01:16:37,492
Please just let me know
what's going on.

689
01:16:37,626 --> 01:16:41,426
What kind of a fucking idiot
do you think I am?

690
01:16:42,564 --> 01:16:44,327
I don't know what you mean.

691
01:16:44,466 --> 01:16:48,163
- Oh, please, Lori.
- Lori?

692
01:16:48,303 --> 01:16:51,966
You're really scaring me, Travis.

693
01:16:54,810 --> 01:16:57,005
You say you know everything.

694
01:16:58,580 --> 01:17:00,639
You know where my dad is?

695
01:17:02,851 --> 01:17:05,786
You said you don't know
where he is.

696
01:17:05,921 --> 01:17:08,685
He left when you were little.

697
01:17:08,824 --> 01:17:12,920
That's right.
He left when I was little.

698
01:17:13,061 --> 01:17:16,553
Left us, left the state.

699
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:20,031
Well, now he's
on death row in Texas.

700
01:17:20,168 --> 01:17:22,398
He murdered two women.

701
01:17:25,040 --> 01:17:27,531
I have the same...

702
01:17:27,676 --> 01:17:29,871
problem that he has.

703
01:17:30,012 --> 01:17:31,877
We see things that
aren't there sometimes.

704
01:17:32,014 --> 01:17:35,142
And the trouble is I don't always know
when it's happening.

705
01:17:38,153 --> 01:17:42,146
So I thought maybe you and Greg weren't
fucking each other behind my back.

706
01:17:42,290 --> 01:17:44,724
I tried really hard
to believe that, Lorraine.

707
01:17:44,860 --> 01:17:47,385
But then he kept shoving it
right in my face.

708
01:17:47,529 --> 01:17:49,861
You think Greg and I...

709
01:17:49,998 --> 01:17:53,092
I'm never gonna
get away from this.

710
01:17:53,235 --> 01:17:56,466
I know that now.
It's inside me.

711
01:18:00,442 --> 01:18:03,206
Did you do something to Greg?

712
01:18:05,180 --> 01:18:07,614
Did I do something to Greg?

713
01:18:09,718 --> 01:18:12,585
Greg did something to me!

714
01:18:15,257 --> 01:18:17,157
Did you hurt him?

715
01:18:18,827 --> 01:18:21,955
You really care about him,
don't you?

716
01:18:22,097 --> 01:18:26,534
Good. I want you to.

717
01:18:29,337 --> 01:18:31,464
What did you do?

718
01:18:31,606 --> 01:18:33,699
You really wanna know?

719
01:18:34,910 --> 01:18:39,074
Oh, God.
What did you do?

720
01:18:42,517 --> 01:18:44,508
See for yourself.

721
01:18:51,693 --> 01:18:54,059
Oh, my God.

722
01:18:55,330 --> 01:18:58,265
You're wrong, Travis.
We didn't do anything.

723
01:18:59,668 --> 01:19:01,863
I swear, there was
nothing going on.

724
01:19:02,003 --> 01:19:05,530
It doesn't even matter
what's real now, Lorraine.

725
01:19:05,674 --> 01:19:08,040
I have to do this.

726
01:19:08,176 --> 01:19:11,577
He wants me to.
I owe him that.

727
01:21:26,448 --> 01:21:28,541
I love you.

728
01:21:29,818 --> 01:21:32,378
My baby boy.

729
01:22:48,063 --> 01:22:51,226
- It's easier to take down my ass.
- It is.

730
01:22:58,873 --> 01:23:03,674
- Why don't you pack the tent?
- Why? I wanna stay here with you.

731
01:23:03,812 --> 01:23:05,939
You all set?

732
01:23:07,048 --> 01:23:08,982
Did you have fun?

733
01:23:10,986 --> 01:23:12,851
I don't mean to beat
a dead horse,

734
01:23:12,988 --> 01:23:15,422
but you know we can't tell
Mom and Alan about this, right?

735
01:23:15,557 --> 01:23:19,152
Can I see? What, you don't want me
to look at them?

736
01:23:19,294 --> 01:23:21,660
He won't let you.
He's got volumes of those pads.

737
01:23:21,796 --> 01:23:23,730
He won't even let me
look at 'em.

738
01:23:23,898 --> 01:23:26,833
If you change your mind,
I'd love to see them.

739
01:23:39,814 --> 01:23:42,647
Oh, shit.

740
01:23:42,784 --> 01:23:44,979
I'm in trouble, Henry.

741
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:49,056
This is so messed up. You weren't
supposed to be back till tomorrow.

742
01:23:49,224 --> 01:23:53,285
- Well, that's not the point, Travis.
- That is the point!

743
01:23:53,428 --> 01:23:55,862
If you came back tomorrow,
you wouldn't know that we went camping

744
01:23:56,031 --> 01:23:57,692
and you wouldn't be upset.

745
01:23:57,832 --> 01:24:00,426
We would have just had a good time
and everything would be fine.

746
01:24:00,568 --> 01:24:02,502
Well, everything wouldn't be fine.

747
01:24:02,670 --> 01:24:04,831
You still did something
very irresponsible.

748
01:24:04,973 --> 01:24:09,000
You should know better than to have him
around a bunch of drunk college kids.

749
01:24:09,144 --> 01:24:11,908
We weren't drunk.
We had a couple of beers.

750
01:24:12,047 --> 01:24:14,572
I'm frickin' 23 years old.
What's the big deal?

751
01:24:14,716 --> 01:24:18,345
Why don't you act like an adult once
in a while instead of a fuckin' baby?

752
01:24:18,486 --> 01:24:20,351
I don't know if
I could trust you now.

753
01:24:20,488 --> 01:24:23,013
Have I ever messed up
before? Ever?

754
01:24:23,158 --> 01:24:26,184
I don't know. I don't know what you've been
doing behind my back.

755
01:24:26,327 --> 01:24:29,455
This is about you not doing
what your mom and I asked.

756
01:24:29,597 --> 01:24:32,691
- This is between Mom and me, Alan, okay?
- Hey!

757
01:24:32,834 --> 01:24:35,166
I live in this house now too, pal.

758
01:24:35,303 --> 01:24:37,737
Well, I can't do anything about that,
can I, asshole?

759
01:24:37,906 --> 01:24:41,569
You better start showing me a little respect.
I'm only gonna put up with so much!

760
01:24:41,709 --> 01:24:44,109
Now look, I'll talk to him, Alan, all right?
I'll talk to him.

761
01:24:44,245 --> 01:24:46,076
Please.

762
01:24:46,214 --> 01:24:48,910
Yeah, see what good that does.

763
01:25:23,751 --> 01:25:25,343
Hey.

764
01:25:33,528 --> 01:25:36,122
Your brother's really
getting it out there.

765
01:25:39,734 --> 01:25:42,396
Some people got it coming.

766
01:25:43,471 --> 01:25:45,132
Right?

767
01:25:55,316 --> 01:25:58,717
You know, we're never
gonna make it as a family

768
01:25:58,853 --> 01:26:02,186
if you guys don't respect me
and listen to what I say.

769
01:26:07,162 --> 01:26:10,188
Sometimes...

770
01:26:10,331 --> 01:26:13,164
I think it's too late
for him and me.

771
01:26:15,203 --> 01:26:17,467
But you're different.

772
01:26:20,742 --> 01:26:23,142
I know you don't say much,

773
01:26:23,278 --> 01:26:25,212
but I can see it in your eyes.

774
01:26:28,016 --> 01:26:31,315
We have a connection.
Don't we?

775
01:26:33,788 --> 01:26:36,052
An understanding.

776
01:26:43,631 --> 01:26:45,690
I can work with you, Henry.

777
01:26:46,834 --> 01:26:49,302
Maybe you'll turn out all right.

778
01:26:54,042 --> 01:26:55,634
You can go.

779
01:27:17,565 --> 01:27:20,864
Go get the phone, will you?
It's in the garage on the workbench.

780
01:27:39,387 --> 01:27:41,048
Thanks.

781
01:27:42,023 --> 01:27:43,615
Hey, Henry.

782
01:27:45,760 --> 01:27:47,387
Hey.

783
01:27:49,564 --> 01:27:51,156
You know her?

784
01:28:00,174 --> 01:28:04,076
Hey, it's me.
You coming over or what?

785
01:28:04,212 --> 01:28:06,271
No, it's no big deal.

786
01:28:06,414 --> 01:28:09,281
He doesn't have to know then.

787
01:28:09,417 --> 01:28:12,909
She doesn't have to know.

788
01:28:13,054 --> 01:28:16,114
I just wanna talk to you
for a little bit about some stuff.

789
01:28:17,592 --> 01:28:19,219
Okay.

790
01:28:20,528 --> 01:28:22,462
She's coming over.

791
01:28:29,671 --> 01:28:31,605
Come on in.

792
01:28:33,808 --> 01:28:36,902
Hey. What are you doing here?

793
01:28:37,045 --> 01:28:38,979
Lori told me you called her.

794
01:28:39,147 --> 01:28:40,546
Yeah. So?

795
01:28:40,682 --> 01:28:44,812
- You gotta stop, man.
- Stop what, being Lori's friend?

796
01:28:44,952 --> 01:28:47,079
If that's why you're here,
you can leave now.

797
01:28:47,221 --> 01:28:50,019
I'm not leaving
until we talk about this.

798
01:28:52,193 --> 01:28:54,423
So that's it?

799
01:28:54,562 --> 01:28:56,427
He has to wash the car?

800
01:28:56,564 --> 01:28:59,089
Now he's having friends over
and everything's back to normal?

801
01:28:59,233 --> 01:29:03,135
I'm getting really tired of you questioning
the way I handle my own kids.

802
01:29:03,271 --> 01:29:05,967
You don't handle them.

803
01:29:06,107 --> 01:29:08,337
You don't even understand them.

804
01:29:10,878 --> 01:29:15,178
Travis wanted to go party with his friends and
his fucked-up brother was holding him back.

805
01:29:15,316 --> 01:29:18,046
So he dragged him in the woods
with a bunch of drunk college kids.

806
01:29:18,186 --> 01:29:22,282
- That's your interpretation.
- No, it's the goddamn truth!

807
01:29:23,791 --> 01:29:26,385
And you're doing
nothing about it.

808
01:29:32,433 --> 01:29:35,368
Henry is not a normal kid.

809
01:29:35,536 --> 01:29:38,096
You can't treat him that way.

810
01:29:38,239 --> 01:29:41,504
You do, and he's gonna snap,
just like his old man.

811
01:29:42,577 --> 01:29:44,442
You should be quiet now.

812
01:29:44,579 --> 01:29:46,911
Lori's not comfortable
being friends right now.

813
01:29:47,982 --> 01:29:49,711
I'll believe that
when she tells me.

814
01:29:49,851 --> 01:29:52,183
What do you think I'm doing here?
You think I'm a mind reader?

815
01:29:52,320 --> 01:29:54,982
She asked me to come
talk to you, Travis.

816
01:29:55,123 --> 01:29:57,648
He sits there all day
watching horror movies

817
01:29:57,792 --> 01:30:00,784
and making all those
fucked-up pictures!

818
01:30:00,928 --> 01:30:04,329
To normal kids,
Henry is a freak.

819
01:30:04,499 --> 01:30:07,696
Don't you ever call him that!

820
01:30:07,835 --> 01:30:10,133
You lost one family.

821
01:30:10,271 --> 01:30:13,035
I'm giving you a second chance.

822
01:30:13,174 --> 01:30:15,199
You gonna blow it again?

823
01:30:15,343 --> 01:30:16,833
Fuck you.

824
01:30:16,978 --> 01:30:19,538
No, fuck you, Alan!

825
01:30:20,615 --> 01:30:23,743
So, what?
You think I'm obsessed with Lori?

826
01:30:23,885 --> 01:30:25,910
You think I'm a stalker
or something?

827
01:30:26,053 --> 01:30:27,816
- If the shoe fits.
- Fuck you!

828
01:30:27,955 --> 01:30:31,254
I'm just telling you the truth.
That's how you're coming across.

829
01:30:31,392 --> 01:30:33,860
You're creeping her out.

830
01:30:34,028 --> 01:30:35,962
Do we have an understanding?

831
01:30:38,666 --> 01:30:41,226
You think I don't hear
what you guys are saying?

832
01:30:41,369 --> 01:30:43,667
What are you talking about?

833
01:30:46,507 --> 01:30:49,442
I know what
you're trying to do to me.

834
01:30:49,577 --> 01:30:52,375
Well, why don't you do it, Bobby?
See what happens.

835
01:30:52,513 --> 01:30:56,916
I don't know what the hell you're talking about,
but do we have an understanding or not?

836
01:30:57,051 --> 01:30:59,178
No, we don't.

837
01:30:59,320 --> 01:31:02,016
Now get the fuck
out of my house!

838
01:31:19,207 --> 01:31:21,607
Henry, help!

839
01:31:34,222 --> 01:31:36,986
Yeah, well, why can't
you take care of it?

840
01:31:37,124 --> 01:31:40,491
Because I have something called a job, Kim.
You should look into it.

841
01:31:40,628 --> 01:31:43,859
All right, I'll take care
of it when I get home.

842
01:31:54,141 --> 01:31:55,733
Hey.

843
01:31:59,146 --> 01:32:01,137
Can I see, huh?

844
01:32:03,417 --> 01:32:05,385
Oh.

845
01:32:05,553 --> 01:32:08,317
Alan took off to go cool down.

846
01:32:09,757 --> 01:32:12,624
He actually put his beer down
and admitted

847
01:32:12,760 --> 01:32:15,092
that he shouldn't argue
when he's drinking.

848
01:32:17,365 --> 01:32:21,267
I think I might have been right
about this one.

849
01:32:21,435 --> 01:32:24,165
There could just be
a decent guy in there.

850
01:32:27,942 --> 01:32:31,742
Are Travis and Bobby
still in his room?

851
01:32:37,118 --> 01:32:39,177
It's really quiet in there.

852
01:33:30,605 --> 01:33:33,073
I know you've had
a tough time so far,

853
01:33:33,240 --> 01:33:36,937
but that doesn't mean you guys
can't be happy from now on.

854
01:33:38,245 --> 01:33:41,703
<i>I love you so much</i>.
